<p>It has come to our attention that unauthorized individuals or fraudsters are circulating fake job offers under the name of our Company. These fraudulent activities typically involve soliciting job applications and requesting applicants to pay processing fees or deposits through deceptive emails, other forms of communication, or fraudulent phone calls. We strongly advise against responding to any unsolicited or fraudulent communication offering a job or interview call in our Company's name, especially if it involves payment of money.</p>
<p>We want to emphasize that our Company follows a merit-based employee selection process. We do not charge any fees or accept any form of payment or security deposit from job seekers during the selection process or while inviting candidates for interviews.</p>
<p>Please note that our Company will not accept any liability for representations made in fraudulent communications or their consequences. Such fraudulent communications should not be considered as offers or representations by our Company.</p>
<p>If you receive a job offer or interview call for any position, we recommend taking certain precautions. You can verify the authenticity of the communication by visiting our official website to obtain contact details. Additionally, you may contact our human resources department to inquire about interview details and any other relevant information.</p>
<p>We urge all concerned parties to remain vigilant and cautious when dealing with job offers or communications claiming to be from our Company. Your safety and security are of utmost importance to us.</p>
<p>Should you suspect that you have fallen victim to fraudulent activity, we urge you to promptly report the incident to your local law enforcement authorities. Additionally, please reach out to us at legal@sharksjob.com to inform us of the situation. Your cooperation in reporting such incidents is crucial in helping us address and prevent further fraudulent activities.</p>

